summary.name: Gapminder Dataset
summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about countries' population, life expectancy, and fertility rates over time.

properties.description: The year in which the data was recorded.
A cluster number assigned to the country based on its characteristics.
The population of the country in the given year.
The average life expectancy of the country's population in the given year.
The average number of children born per woman in the country in the given year.

goals.question: What is the trend of population over time?
goals.visualization: Line chart of population against year
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if the population of countries has been increasing or decreasing over time.

goals.question: What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of life expectancy against fertility rate
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is a correlation between life expectancy and fertility rate.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the range of life expectancy across countries.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility rate across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the range of fertility rate across countries.

goals.question: What is the distribution of countries across clusters?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of cluster against number of countries
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the distribution of countries across different clusters.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for country in data['country'].unique():
        country_data = data[data['country'] == country]
        ax.plot(country_data['year'], country_data['pop'], label=country)
    
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Population')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of population over time?')
    ax.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1), title='Country')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['life_expect'], data['fertility'], c=data['cluster'], cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    ax.set_ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?')
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Clusters")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['life_expect'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['life_expect'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['life_expect'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    cluster_counts = data['cluster'].value_counts()
    ax = cluster_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='c')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of countries across clusters?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Cluster")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Countries")
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    ax.legend(["Countries"])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
